Edit->Copy

"Copy" copies the selected object(s) onto a 3D clipboard. The contents
of the clipboard can then be "pasted" back into the Movieola scene, or
by another program like SceneViewer or Showcase.

The 3D clipboard can only contain one buffer at one time. You can use
Edit->Show Clipboard to view the contents of the clipboard. The
clipboard contents don't change until you do a "Cut" or "Copy" again.

NOTE: If you are going to paste the selection back to the scene, to
make an identical copy, use "Duplicate" rather than "Copy" and
"Paste". It is not only easier, but also memory-efficient, because
only one copy of the geometry is maintained as far as possible. This
is particularly relevant for scenes with zillions of identical
geometries (Example: a city).
